{"word":"χολάω","slug":"χολάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>χολάω</b></el> <el>(χολάω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:χολή'><el>χολή</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be full of black bile, to be melancholy mad</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <el>χολόομαι</el>, <i>to be angry</i>, <b><a href='S:Moschus'>Mosch.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}